The paper deals with the problem of detecting faults and unhealthy conditions in High Performance Computing Systems, which is a topic related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The method proposed uses a type of neural network called autoncoder, which is a technique commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the impact of the approach on the computing units performance, which is a topic related to Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
